---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
    title="Starting a Daycare | Childcare Business Plan"
    description="Your daycare business starts with understanding what makes your market unique. Get personalized insights based on your state's regulations and market conditions."
>
    <main class="max-w-4xl mx-auto py-16 px-4">
        <!-- 1. OWNERSHIP FRAMING -->
        <section class="text-center mb-16">
            <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">
                YOUR Daycare Business
            </h1>
            <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
                Starting a daycare isn't a one-size-fits-all journey. Your
                state, your capacity, and your market create a unique
                opportunity that generic advice can't capture.
            </p>
        </section>

        <!-- 2. FACTORS THAT AFFECT OUTCOME -->
        <section class="mb-16">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">
                What Affects Your Success
            </h2>
            <div class="prose prose-lg text-gray-600">
                <p class="mb-4">
                    Every daycare operates under different conditions that
                    dramatically impact both startup costs and income potential.
                    Your state's licensing requirements might allow you to care
                    for 6 children or 12. Your local regulations might require
                    extensive renovations or minimal changes. Your market might
                    support premium rates or demand budget-friendly options.
                </p>
                <p class="mb-4">
                    These variables aren't just details—they're the foundation
                    of your business model. A home daycare in Vermont operates
                    under completely different constraints than a center in
                    Texas. The path that works for one won't work for the other.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Beyond regulations, your local competition, demographic
                    composition, and even zoning laws create opportunities and
                    limitations unique to your situation. Understanding your
                    specific landscape is the first step to building a
                    sustainable business.
                </p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- 3. WHY GENERIC ADVICE FAILS -->
        <section class="mb-16">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">
                Why Online Advice Often Conflicts
            </h2>
            <div class="prose prose-lg text-gray-600">
                <p class="mb-4">
                    You've probably noticed that every article about starting a
                    daycare tells a different story. One says you need $50,000
                    to start, another says $5,000. One recommends starting small
                    from home, another insists you need a commercial space from
                    day one.
                </p>
                <p class="mb-4">
                    They're both right—for someone. The problem is that generic
                    advice assumes conditions that might be completely different
                    from yours. What works in one regulatory environment becomes
                    impossible in another. What's profitable in one market loses
                    money in the next.
                </p>
                <p>
                    This is why personalization isn't a luxury—it's a necessity.
                    You need to see the numbers for your state, your capacity,
                    and your market before you can make confident decisions
                    about your business.
                </p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- 4. CTA TO CALCULATOR -->
        <section class="text-center py-12 px-8 glass-panel rounded-3xl">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
                See How Much YOU Could Make in Your State
            </h2>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
                Get your personalized income estimate based on your state's
                regulations and your business model.
            </p>
            <a
                href="/tools/income-builder"
                class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-teal-600 hover:bg-teal-700 text-white font-medium px-8 py-4 shadow-lg transition-all"
            >
                Use the Free Calculator →
            </a>
        </section>
    </main>
</Layout>
